{"word":"εὐχετάομαι","slug":"εὐχετάομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐχετάομαι</b></el> <el>(εὐχετάομαι,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in epic <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a> <el>εὐχετόωνται, -όωντο</el>, <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <el>-άασθαι</el>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εὔχομαι'><el>εὔχομαι</el></a>\n<p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to pray</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <i>to make vows</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to boast oneself, profess, brag, boast</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>τίνες ἔμμεναι εὐχετόωνται</el>; <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>ἐπ' ἀνδράσιν εὐχ.</el> <i>to glory</i> over them, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}